<title>GERMANY: Schmalbach Lubeca to take over JCI unit.</title>
<headline>Schmalbach Lubeca to take over JCI unit.</headline>
<dateline>RATINGEN, Germany 1996-12-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>German packaging producer Schmalbach-Lubeca AG, a unit of giant utility Viag AG said on Monday it would take over U.S. group Johnson Controls Inc's PET unit at the start of 1997.</p>
<p>In a mandatory statement, Schmalbach Lubeca said the PET unit had sales of 1.2 billion marks in 1996 and staff of around 2,300.</p>
<p>Terms were not disclosed. Schmalbach Lubeca said final contract details and cartel office approval were still outstanding.</p>
<p>The acquisition would advance its aim to become a leading producer of PET applications, the German firm said, adding that it expected its sales in this area to reach around 1.9 billion marks in 1997.</p>
<p>-- Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
